M a l e: Protarsomeres 1 to 3 weakly widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 93, 94
) 0.40 mm long, symmetrical, well sclerotized. Apical process of median lobe obliquely inflexed, shorter than basal bulb, with blunt tip and dorsally split valves; articular process inconspicuous. Parameres almost evenly wide between bases and apices, slightly bent in dorsal view, straight in lateral view. Internal sac lacking sclerites, vesicular, bearing very dense, minute spine-like structures.
